b01efe90-f301-41ba-b46a-d609e8fa44e4.title: Fritz the Glassblower
b01efe90-f301-41ba-b46a-d609e8fa44e4.text:
Ah <player>, have you come to sell me some molten
glass?

d81cb2dd-2684-4552-945b-5583a72ed75b.title: Fritz the Glassblower
d81cb2dd-2684-4552-945b-5583a72ed75b.text:
...errr, well should you get any I'm quite happy to pay
for it. Remember, I'll pay you 20 gold pieces for each
piece of molten glass you get for me.

54228176-22ed-4258-9256-0cc63a695cc7.title: Fritz the Glassblower
54228176-22ed-4258-9256-0cc63a695cc7.text: So what did you want to talk to me about then?

options.text: Could you tell me how to make molten glass again, please?
I just thought I'd drop in and say hello.

cc18ad9c-ebbf-4053-8ced-3873baada405.title: <player>
cc18ad9c-ebbf-4053-8ced-3873baada405.text: I just thought I'd drop in and say hello.

c88f09c6-7dcf-46ce-b03c-9c52c5b660d9.title: Fritz the Glassblower
c88f09c6-7dcf-46ce-b03c-9c52c5b660d9.text:
Hello then. I'm afraid I don't have any time to chat
though. The druids of Taverley have placed a huge
order for glass vials, so I'm very busy.

22fd2721-50b9-4b41-95ed-08e1742f7d88.title: Fritz the Glassblower
22fd2721-50b9-4b41-95ed-08e1742f7d88.text:
Umm, not much point me trying to pay you for glass
you don't have, is there?

b3f3f5a8-540c-4488-a9b1-e97434061c7a.title: <player>
b3f3f5a8-540c-4488-a9b1-e97434061c7a.text: Well, actually, if you don't mind...

74f834ec-eabe-49cd-aadd-ba546ccb5578.title: Fritz the Glassblower
74f834ec-eabe-49cd-aadd-ba546ccb5578.text:
I guess you've never heard of a rhetorical question
then. I'll make it simple for you. You bring glass, me
pay shiny gold coins.

cca7f140-7b78-4416-88cb-0642baa2cab1.title: <player>
cca7f140-7b78-4416-88cb-0642baa2cab1.text:
Could you tell me how to make molten glass again,
please?

69b760ba-c035-4393-9300-24e75e5088fc.title: Note
69b760ba-c035-4393-9300-24e75e5088fc.text: There is a thing where he will tell u how to make the first time u talk to him

4507b02c-e2d6-4f20-be39-71c56ce07c11.title: Fritz the Glassblower
4507b02c-e2d6-4f20-be39-71c56ce07c11.text:
Well, I am very busy at the moment, but I guess I
can take 5 minutes off for my favourite student.

975b1fa6-0c4c-4c63-8e34-3850575f2f2e.title: Fritz the Glassblower
975b1fa6-0c4c-4c63-8e34-3850575f2f2e.text:
Glass is made from soda ash and silica. We get our
soda ash by collecting seaweed from the rocks - the
prevailing currents make the north-west corner of the
island the best place to find it, it can also be found in

3c1667d9-8351-40a0-b3ce-128f8a820e4b.title: Fritz the Glassblower
3c1667d9-8351-40a0-b3ce-128f8a820e4b.text:
your nets sometimes when you're fishing, on Karamja
island or at the Piscatoris Fishing Colony in the nets
there. To turn seaweed into soda ash, all you need to
do is burn it on a fire. Feel free to use the range in

956af55d-48da-45fa-9220-a798d93d1b2b.title: Fritz the Glassblower
956af55d-48da-45fa-9220-a798d93d1b2b.text:
my house for that; it's the one directly west of here.
Next we collect sand from the sandpit that you'll also
find just west of here, there are others located in
Yanille and Shilo Village.

021dcc59-925e-4f5d-9d01-8fd30c8316a2.title: Fritz the Glassblower
021dcc59-925e-4f5d-9d01-8fd30c8316a2.text: You can use the bucket I gave you earlier.

2d32aa20-531f-4ee2-9b27-f1971edacd5d.title: Fritz the Glassblower
2d32aa20-531f-4ee2-9b27-f1971edacd5d.text:
Bring the sand and the soda ash back here and melt
them together in the furnace, and there you have it -
molten glass!

9d1e2aa2-2360-4a90-814d-ae8b6fd0124b.title: Fritz the Glassblower
9d1e2aa2-2360-4a90-814d-ae8b6fd0124b.text:
There are many things you can use the molten glass
for once you have made it. Depending on how talented
you are, you could try turning it into something, like a
fishbowl, for example. If you'd like to try your hand at

4139d0c2-ba89-4267-9a6e-6ec00dc83b27.title: Fritz the Glassblower
4139d0c2-ba89-4267-9a6e-6ec00dc83b27.text:
the fine art of glassblowing you can use my spare
glassblowing pipe. I think I left it on the chest of
drawers in my house this morning.

38a2b846-5545-45b2-9861-c6917db2fe11.title: Fritz the Glassblower
38a2b846-5545-45b2-9861-c6917db2fe11.text:
Alternatively I am always happy to buy the molten glass
from you, saves me running about making it for
myself.

349d89c7-327d-4337-87d7-38a8e8803d9b.title: <player>
349d89c7-327d-4337-87d7-38a8e8803d9b.text: That sounds good. How much will you pay me?

4e20ca1e-18e7-4f3c-9cc4-6cc1093bf2ea.title: Fritz the Glassblower
4e20ca1e-18e7-4f3c-9cc4-6cc1093bf2ea.text:
Tell you what, because you've been interested in my
art, I'll pay you the premium price of 20 gold pieces
for each piece of molten glass you bring me.

abb4816d-1ecf-45d7-8cbb-df3dcd174feb.title: Fritz the Glassblower
abb4816d-1ecf-45d7-8cbb-df3dcd174feb.text:
Fantastic! Let's see, for that much glass I could pay
you ...

79d035fd-8ac8-472c-8b69-987259c66da0.title: <player>
79d035fd-8ac8-472c-8b69-987259c66da0.text:
Are you mad? I've run all over the island to make this
glass.

a194b768-ac04-4386-9d43-e5923b548acc.title: Fritz the Glassblower
a194b768-ac04-4386-9d43-e5923b548acc.text:
Pity. Well you can find me here if you change your
mind.

options.text: Are you mad? I've run all over the island to make this glass.
Sure, that sounds like a fair price.

1a213b65-1c79-49af-a757-f46736d86c37.title: <player>
1a213b65-1c79-49af-a757-f46736d86c37.text: Sure, that sounds like a fair price.

59e5425c-854f-46f9-90c7-324c4dba18fe.title: Fritz the Glassblower
59e5425c-854f-46f9-90c7-324c4dba18fe.text:
Thanks very much, msblueyes. I'll buy any more that
you bring.
